    • isIndexNumeric

      public static boolean isIndexNumeric​(Store store, Condition condition)
      This function takes the Store and a Condition as an argument, and returns a boolean if the column associated with the condition is indexed as a numeric value

      The associated column will be a numeric value if it is a list of numbers, dates or time stamps.

      Parameters:
      store - This argument specifies the store we are using. Each store has its own Java object, that describes its data structure.
      condition - This argument is the condition, that was specified in the query. Each condition lays a restriction on particular store column.
      Returns:
      It returns a boolean indicating, if the column associated with the condition is indexed as a numeric value.

    • isRangeType

      public static boolean isRangeType​(Store store, Condition condition)
      This function takes the Store and a Condition as an argument, and returns a boolean if the column associated with the condition is a type of a range.

      For example AA10-1004 is a range type with values as AA10, AA11,... AA1003, AA1004.

      Parameters:
      store - This argument specifies the store we are using. Each store has its own Java object, that describes its data structure.
      condition - This argument is the condition, that was specified in the query. Each condition lays a restriction on particular store column.
      Returns:
      It returns a boolean indicating, if the column associated with the condition is of data type range.

    • mergeIndexNodes

      public static java.util.ArrayList<SdqlNode> mergeIndexNodes​(java.util.ArrayList<SdqlNode> currentValue, java.util.ArrayList<SdqlNode> nextValue)
      This function takes two sorted lists of Sdql Nodes and returns a merged and sorted list.
      Parameters:
      currentValue - nodes is the present, merged sorted list of nodes satisfying conditions so far.
      nextValue - nodes is the next qualifying nodes matching the next criteria. This will be merged with current value nodes
      Returns:
      This functions returns the sorted merged list of currentValue Nodes and nextValue nodes. Sorting is done based on lower bound and upper bound number of the node.
